                <h2>Step 4: The Geometry of the Trimmer</h2>

                <p>The difference between a "wizard on the subway" and a highly paid CEO is strictly where they trim their borders. You must create sharp architectural intention.</p>

                <h3>The Neckline Disaster</h3>
                <p>The single worst aesthetic mistake a man can make is trimming his neckline directly exactly on the curve of his chinbone. This makes the chin look impossibly small and creates a horrifying "double-chin" illusion. The neckline must remain drastically lower to create heavy visual weight on the jaw.</p>
                <p><strong>The Golden Rule:</strong> Place two horizontal fingers exactly above the top of your Adam's apple. Where your top finger sits is the boundary line. Shave everything below that line totally bald. Leave everything above it entirely massive. This creates a square, violently masculine jawline profile.</p>

